const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Electrolux Professional the same as residential Electrolux?",
    a: "No — this is the most important disambiguation on this page. Electrolux Professional is a separate public company (Nasdaq: EPRO) since a corporate spin-off from Electrolux AB in 2020. Separate parts catalogs, separate service network, separate engineering. A residential Electrolux dishwasher repair does not translate to a commercial Electrolux Professional repair, and vice versa. This matters operationally: if you're sourcing parts or calling for service, specify 'Electrolux Professional' (or the model prefix EP20/EP30/EP40/green&clean/Premium) so the service desk routes you correctly. Calling 'Electrolux dishwasher repair' without the Professional qualifier usually lands you with residential parts and the wrong service approach."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between green&clean and Premium?",
    a: "green&clean is Electrolux Professional's standard commercial line — undercounter rack machines, hood passthrough, and smaller rack conveyor configurations for mid-volume commercial operations. Premium is the flagship conveyor family, engineered for high-volume institutional operations: hotel banquet prep, large cafeteria systems, university dining commons, stadium commissary kitchens. Both share engineering fundamentals but Premium has heavier build quality, larger wash and rinse capacity, and is engineered for 18+ hour-per-day duty cycles. Preparation is a third line — pass-through and door-type for preparation kitchens and small-to-mid institutional operations below Premium's scale."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Electrolux Professional at LA institutional kitchens (USC, UCLA, LAX)?",
    a: "Yes. Electrolux Professional's LA presence concentrates in the institutional segment: USC University Village and Campus Center dining operations, UCLA dining commons peripherals (not the flagship Bruin Plate, which runs domestic brands, but several satellite kitchen operations), LAX airline-catering commissaries (Gate Gourmet runs a mixed fleet that includes EP Premium conveyors), and large hotel commissary operations at downtown and beach-corridor properties. Institutional service includes documented maintenance records appropriate for facility-department equipment-replacement-reserve reporting and HACCP compliance files."
  },
  {
    q: "Is my EP warranty affected by independent repair?",
    a: "Consult your specific warranty documentation, but the general framework: Electrolux Professional's warranty program typically requires authorized service provider involvement during the warranty period. Using an independent service like ours during warranty can affect coverage. Our work is primarily post-warranty, emergency response when authorized-provider dispatch doesn't fit the operator's timing, and out-of-warranty units beyond the coverage period. For warranty work on a newer Electrolux Professional, contact EP directly or your authorized dealer; for everything else, we're an option."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Electrolux Professional commercial dishwasher repair cost in LA?",
    a: "$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Typical EP service ranges: door gasket $180–$320, door switch $160–$260, fill valve $220–$380, rinse-arm bearing $200–$360, thermostat $200–$340, booster element $360–$580, wash pump seal kit $380–$620, wash pump rebuild $500–$820, Premium conveyor drive service $600–$1,200, Premium tank heater $700–$1,400, control board $700–$1,350. Most EP green&clean calls land $380–$750 parts-and-labor; Premium conveyor jobs run $600–$1,500. Parts supply via EP's US distribution — typically 3–7 days on specialty components from Charlotte, NC distribution hub."
  }
];

