  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Electrolux Professional — separate public company since 2020</h2>
      <p>
        This page exists to make a disambiguation clear. There are two Electrolux companies, and their products are
        not interchangeable. <b>Electrolux AB</b> is the Swedish residential white-goods company — refrigerators,
        washing machines, residential dishwashers, residential ovens. <b>Electrolux Professional</b> (Nasdaq: EPRO)
        is a separate public company as of a March 2020 spin-off from Electrolux AB. EP makes commercial foodservice
        and commercial laundry equipment, and operates an entirely distinct parts, service, and engineering
        organization from residential Electrolux.
      </p>
      <p>
        This matters for every service call. Parts cataloged for residential Electrolux do not fit commercial
        Electrolux Professional equipment, and vice versa. Service technicians trained on residential Electrolux
        are not automatically trained on EP commercial. If you're ordering parts or scheduling service, specify
        "Electrolux Professional" or reference the specific model prefix (green&clean, Premium, Preparation, or
        EP20/EP30/EP40 model numbers) so you're routed to the commercial catalog and commercial service network
        rather than residential.
      </p>
      <p>
        Electrolux Professional's broader brand family includes several related commercial brands: Dito Electrolux
        (commercial food preparation equipment), Dishlex (Australia/New Zealand market), Molteni (Paris-based
        ultra-premium range manufacturer), Zanussi Professional (European commercial kitchen equipment), WASCOMAT
        (commercial laundry, US presence), and Grindmaster-Cecilware (commercial beverage equipment). This Dishwasher
        Repair page is EP's commercial dishwasher scope specifically; related EP-family equipment is covered on
        other sdar-v2 pages as those ship.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

