      <h2>LA institutional cluster — where EP lives</h2>
      <p>
        Electrolux Professional's LA presence concentrates in the institutional and large-scale foodservice segment.
        USC's University Village dining operations run EP equipment across multiple locations. UCLA's peripheral
        dining sites (not the flagship Bruin Plate facility, which runs domestic brands, but several satellite
        kitchen operations serving residential colleges and campus retail) include EP commercial dishwashers.
      </p>
      <p>
        LAX airline-catering commissaries are EP's most visible high-volume LA presence. Gate Gourmet operates a
        mixed fleet of commercial dishwashers across its LAX flight-kitchen operations, including EP Premium
        conveyors on some production lines alongside Meiko M-iQ flight-types and Hobart FT900 flight-types. Large
        downtown and beach-corridor hotel commissary operations — the off-property food-production facilities that
        supply multiple hotels within a single operator's portfolio — also run EP Premium conveyors for their
        ware-washing needs.
      </p>
      <p>
        Institutional service has specific requirements: documented maintenance records for facility-department
        equipment-replacement-reserve reporting, HACCP compliance documentation, Joint Commission inspection-ready
        service logs at healthcare-adjacent institutional accounts. We provide service documentation appropriate
        for these record-keeping requirements alongside standard work orders.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Spin-off 2020 — separate parts chain from residential Electrolux</h2>
      <p>
        The March 2020 spin-off of Electrolux Professional from Electrolux AB created two operationally separate
        companies. Before 2020, commercial Electrolux operations ran within Electrolux AB alongside residential;
        after 2020, they run as Electrolux Professional AB under independent ownership structure (Nasdaq: EPRO). For
        parts sourcing, this means the commercial parts catalog, the commercial warranty program, and the commercial
        service network operate independently from residential.
      </p>
      <p>
        Pre-2020 commercial Electrolux equipment typically has parts continuity through the post-2020 EP parts
        chain, since EP inherited the commercial catalog at spin-off. But operators searching for "Electrolux parts"
        generically often land in residential catalogs where the parts don't fit commercial equipment. We see this
        operator confusion regularly — someone orders what they think is a commercial part from residential
        Electrolux and it arrives incompatible. Our techs source through EP's commercial distribution specifically,
        so we don't hit this failure mode.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

